# Copy to .env (or .env.local) for local dev. Variables prefixed with
# EXPO_PUBLIC_ are inlined into the JS bundle at build time.

# FastAPI backend URL.
# Defaults to 10.0.2.2:8000 when unset (the special Android-emulator IP that
# routes to the host machine's localhost). For a real phone on the same Wi-Fi,
# replace with your dev machine's LAN IP, e.g. http://192.168.1.42:8000.
EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://10.0.2.2:8000

# Sentry crash reporting (src/lib/sentry.ts). Unset = Sentry never initialises
# (the app behaves exactly as before). To ENABLE, add the key WITH a real DSN
# value to the eas.json preview/production env blocks — do NOT add it there as
# an empty string: EAS rejects an empty env value ("not allowed to be empty")
# and every build fails (CI's `expo export` won't catch it). Leave it off
# locally so dev crashes stay out of the dashboard. A DSN is a publishable
# client-side id, safe to commit. Do NOT add the Sentry Expo config plugin to
# app.json for source maps — it breaks the gradle build (see CLAUDE.md).
# EXPO_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN=
